fields.name: Colombia - San Pancho
fields.description: The most popular coffee from one of the top high quality producing countries. Grown in an archeological UNESCO world heritage site.  Coffee farming within the region is overwhelmingly small-scale. Approximately 80% of producers from the region farm coffee on less than 3 hectares of land. These small farms are tended by individual families with labour only very rarely being contracted out. All cherries are hand-picked, which leads to more thorough and intensive management practices and great pride in the final product .
